>Accusative total objects<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h3><strong>6. Consonant gradation in nouns<\/strong><\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/wordtype-a-consonant-gradation-sanatyyppi-astevaihtelu\/\">Wordtype A \u2013 KPT<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/wordtype-b-consonant-gradation-sanatyypit-astevaihtelu\/\"><strong>Wordtype B \u2013 KPT<\/strong><\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div><\/div>\n<div  class=\"lgc-column lgc-grid-parent lgc-grid-50 lgc-tablet-grid-100 lgc-mobile-grid-100 lgc-equal-heights \"><div  class=\"inside-grid-column\">\n<h3><strong>7. The plural partitive case<br \/>\n<\/strong><\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/the-partitive-plural-monikon-partitiivi\/\">The plural partitive<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/grammatical-cases\/plural-partitive-of-long-words\/\">Plural partitive of long words<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/syntax\/sentence-types\/t-plural-vs-partitive-plural\/\">Plural partitive vs T-plural<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/finnish-cases\/grammatical-cases\/plural-partitive-vs-plural-genitive\"><strong>Plural partitive vs plural genitive<\/strong><\/a><\/li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/morphology\/kissa-words-in-the-plural-partitive\">List:<em> Kissa<\/em>-words<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/morphology\/koira-words-in-the-plural-partitive\">List: <em>Koira<\/em>-words<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h3><strong>8. The plural genitive case<br \/>\n<\/strong><\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/the-genitive-plural-monikon-genetiivi\/\">The plural genitive<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/grammatical-cases\/the-plural-genitive-of-long-words\/\">Plural genitive of long words<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/finnish-cases\/grammatical-cases\/when-to-use-the-plural-genitive-case\">Using the plural genitive<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h3><strong>9. The plural location cases<\/strong><\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/plural-location-cases-monikon-paikallissijat\/\">The plural location cases<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/location-cases\/plural-illative-suomalaisiin-ihmisiin\/\">The plural illative<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/finnish-cases\/grammatical-cases\/plural-translative-case-finnish-grammar\">The plural translative<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/morphology\/the-plural-forms-in-finnish-examples\">Examples of the plural cases<\/a><\/strong><\/p>\n<h3><strong>10. Rarer cases<\/strong><\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/the-translative-case-ksi-translatiivi\/\">The translative (-<em>ksi<\/em>)<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/the-essive-case-na-essiivi\/\">The essive (-<em>na<\/em>)<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/the-abessive-case-tta-tta-abessiivi\/\">The abessive (-<em>tta<\/em>)<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/the-comitative-case-komitatiivi\/\">The comitative (-<em>ine<\/em>)<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/instructive-instruktiivi-nain-sen-omin-silmin\/\"><strong>The instructive (-<em>in<\/em>)<\/strong><\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h3><strong>11. Fossilized cases<\/strong><\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/morphology\/postitse-puhelimitse-ohitse-maitse-prolative\/\">Prolative: <em>puhelimitse vesitse<\/em><\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/location-cases\/the-lative-case-ylos-alas-kauemmas-finnish-grammar\/\"><strong>Lative: <\/strong><em><strong>alas ulos yl\u00f6s<\/strong><\/em><\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div><\/div><div class=\"lgc-clear\"><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n<div class=\"su-spoiler su-spoiler-style-fancy su-spoiler-icon-caret\" data-scroll-offset=\"0\" data-anchor-in-url=\"no\"><div class=\"su-spoiler-title\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\"><span class=\"su-spoiler-icon\"><\/span>Inflection types of nouns<\/div><div class=\"su-spoiler-content su-u-clearfix su-u-trim\">\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center; color: #86ad40;\"><strong>INFLECTION TYPES OF NOUNS<br \/>\n<\/strong><\/h2>\n<div  class=\"lgc-column lgc-grid-parent lgc-grid-50 lgc-tablet-grid-100 lgc-mobile-grid-100 lgc-equal-heights \"><div  class=\"inside-grid-column\">\n<h3><strong>1. Words ending in <em>-i<\/em><\/strong><\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-vocabulary\/words-ending-in\/inflection-of-words-like-uusi-kasi-vuosi-kuukausi\">Inflection of words like UUSI<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-vocabulary\/words-ending-in\/list-of-old-words-ending-in-i-of-the-ovi-type\">Inflection of words like OVI<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-vocabulary\/words-ending-in\/li-ni-ri-words-inflection-of-words-like-pieni\">Inflection of words like PIENI<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-vocabulary\/words-ending-in\/special-partitive-cases-toimi-toimea-tointa-kotus-wordtype-25\">Inflection of words like TOIMI<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-vocabulary\/words-ending-in\/old-words-versus-new-words-ending-in-i\/\">Old\/New words ending in<em> -i<\/em><\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h3><strong>2. Words ending in a consonant<\/strong><\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-vocabulary\/words-ending-in\/inflection-of-words-ending-in-a-consonant\">Words ending in a consonant<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-vocabulary\/words-ending-in\/us-ukse-versus-us-ude\/\"><em>Us-Ukse-<\/em> vs <em>Us-Ude-<\/em> words<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-vocabulary\/words-ending-in\/words-ending-in-is-kallis-kaunis-futis-roskis-kasvis\/\">Words ending in <em>-is<\/em><\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h3><strong>3. Special inflection cases<\/strong><\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/the-inflection-of-the-numbers\/\">Inflection of numbers<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/ordinal-numbers-in-the-cases-jarjestysnumerot\/\">Inflection of ordinal numbers<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/blog-posts\/missa-asut-tampereella-vai-helsingissa\/\">Inflection of place names<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/uusikielemme.fi\/finnish-grammar\/finnish-cases\/interesting-inflection\/inflection-of-foreign-names-in-finnish\">Inflection of foreign names<\/a><\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong><a h